==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Widal reaction
<hw>Wi*dal" reaction</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[After
Fernand <etsep>Widal</etsep> (b. 1862), French physician.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A test for typhoid fever based on the fact that
blood serum of one affected, in a bouillon culture of typhoid bacilli,
causes the bacilli to agglutinate and lose their motility.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Widdy</ent>⟦br⟧
